eral is a hard requirement for PDM microphones partitioning MCUs into compatible and incompatible#{11}":[48,49]},"outlinks":[{"title":"communication","target":"communication","line":7},{"title":"sensors","target":"sensors","line":8},{"title":"rp2040-pio-state-machines-implement-custom-protocols-at-hardware-speed","target":"rp2040-pio-state-machines-implement-custom-protocols-at-hardware-speed","line":43},{"title":"esp32-i2c-is-software-implemented-and-remappable-to-any-gpio-pair","target":"esp32-i2c-is-software-implemented-and-remappable-to-any-gpio-pair","line":44},{"title":"communication","target":"communication","line":47},{"title":"sensors","target":"sensors","line":48}],"metadata":{"description":"PDM/I2S microphones like the SPH0645LM4H require a hardware I2S peripheral — you cannot bit-bang I2S at audio sample rates on an 8-bit AVR. This creates a binary MCU compatibility gate: either you have hardware I2S or you cannot use this sensor class at all","type":"claim","source":"docs/parts/adafruit-pdm-microphone-sph0645lm4h-digital-audio-3v3.md","confidence":"proven","topics":["[[communication]]","[[sensors]]"],"related_components":["adafruit-pdm-microphone-sph0645lm4h","esp32-devkit-v1","rp2040"]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[]},